  "text": "Decreased cell viability is a comprehensive response, which reflects the functional state of cells in a number of aspects. Inhibition of cell proliferation, induction of apoptosis or autophagy, and cytotoxic necrosis all decrease cell viability. Yu et al [CITATION_1] demonstrated that resveratrol decreases cell viability by way of the induction of apoptosis and G 2 /M-phase cell cycle arrest. However, Opipari et al (2�) identified that resveratrol induces cell death in ovarian cancer A2780 cells via a mechanism distinct from apoptosis. Neither apoptotic pathways associated with Bcl-2 and Bcl-xL nor activation of caspase-9 were demonstrated to be required for the resveratrol-induced death of A2780 cells. Furthermore, decreased cell viability associated with the induction of autophagy was observed in breast cancer stem-like cells following treatment with resveratrol [CITATION_2] .",
